fr:mainmatter.html:p:
Give a vector field v_t one can construct a time-dependent diffeomorphic map called a flow \phi : [0,1] \times  \mathbb {R}^d \to  \mathbb {R}^d defined via the ordinary differential equation
\begin {align*}
  \frac {\mathrm {d}}{\mathrm {d}t} \phi _t(x) &= v_t(\phi _t(x)) \\
  \phi _{0}(x) &= x
.\end {align*}

